'''城市绿地'''為城市中用作[[公園|公園]]或其他綠地的[[都市開放空間|開放空間]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www3.epa.gov/region1/eco/uep/openspace.html|title=What is Open Space/Green Space?|publisher=United States Environmental Protection Agency|access-date=2021-04-30|archive-date=2021-06-01|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210601233136/https://www3.epa.gov/region1/eco/uep/openspace.html}}</ref>，[[世界衛生組織|世界衛生組織]]將其定義為「有任何植被覆蓋的城市土地」<ref name=":5" />，可能伴隨著[[遊樂場|遊樂場]]、[[蓝色空间|蓝色空间]]（水體或水道）等人工設施或[[自然景觀|自然景觀]]，有休憩、生態、美觀與健康等用途<ref name=":5">{{Cite book|title=Urban green spaces: a brief for action|publisher=World Health Organization Regional Office for Europe|year=2017|location=UN City, Denmark}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal |last1=Jayasinghe |first1=DBC |last2=Hemakumara |first2=GPTS |last3=Hewage |first3=P |title=GIS-Based Assessment of the Green Space Per Capita in the City of Galle, Sri Lanka |journal=Sri Lanka Journal of Advanced Social Studies |date=2018 |volume=7 |issue=2 |pages=3–24 |url=https://www.ncas.ac.lk/journal/journal_17-18/GIS-Based.pdf |access-date=29 December 2020 |publisher=NCAS |location=Sri Lanka |archive-date=2021-04-30 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210430001809/https://www.ncas.ac.lk/journal/journal_17-18/GIS-Based.pdf }}</ref>。城市綠地有時為大學校園、{{le|社區花園|Community gardening}}等私人或機構的用地，但一般均對公眾開放，位於城市範圍以外的[[州立公園|州立公園]]和[[國家公園|國家公園]]則不屬於城市绿地。早在一世紀[[古羅馬|古羅馬]]即有{{lang|la|rus in urbe}}（意指城市中的鄉村）的概念，將綠地融入城市規劃中<ref name=":1">{{Cite news|url=http://urbanrambles.org/background/a-brief-history-of-rus-in-urbe-1307|title=A brief history of urban green spaces|date=2015-12-28|work=Urban Rambles|access-date=2018-10-25|archive-date=2021-05-01|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210501043338/http://urbanrambles.org/background/a-brief-history-of-rus-in-urbe-1307}}</ref><ref name=":2">{{cite journal |last1=Giovagnorio |first1=Ilaria |last2=Usai |first2=Daniela |last3=Palmas |first3=Alessandro |last4=Chiri |first4=Giovanni Marco |title=The environmental elements of foundations in Roman cities: A theory of the architect Gaetano Vinaccia |journal=Sustainable Cities and Society |date=July 2017 |volume=32 |pages=42–55 |doi=10.1016/j.scs.2017.03.002 }}</ref>，現代城市綠地則可追溯至十七至十八世紀英國[[倫敦|倫敦]]的城市廣場<ref>{{cite journal |last1=Lawrence |first1=Henry W. |title=The Greening of the Squares of London: Transformation of Urban landscapes and Ideals |journal=Annals of the Association of American Geographers |date=March 1993 |volume=83 |issue=1 |pages=90–118 |doi=10.1111/j.1467-8306.1993.tb01924.x }}</ref>。

城市綠地可減緩[[地表逕流|地表逕流]]與[[熱島效應|熱島效應]]<ref name= Yujia54>{{cite journal |last1=Zhanga |first1=Yujia |last2=Murray |first2=Alan |last3=Turner |first3=B |title=Optimizing green space locations to reduce daytime and nighttime urban heat island effects in Phoenix, Arizona |journal=Landscape and Urban Planning |date=Sep 2017 |volume=165 |pages=162–171 |doi=10.1016/j.landurbplan.2017.04.009 }}</ref>，還可降低[[空氣污染|空氣污染]]，對周圍社區的居民生理和心理健康有正面影響<ref name=Shishegar43>{{cite journal |last1=Shishegar |first1=Nastaran |title=The Impact of Green Areas on Mitigating Urban Heat Island Effect: A Review |journal=The International Journal of Environmental Sustainability |date=Jan 2013 |volume=9 |issue=1 |pages=119–130 |url=https://www.researchgate.net/publication/271206461|doi=10.18848/2325-1077/CGP/v09i01/55081 }}</ref><ref>{{cite journal |last1=Maas |first1=Jolanda |last2=Verheij |first2=Robert A. |last3=Groenewegen |first3=Peter P. |last4=Vries |first4=Sjerp de |last5=Spreeuwenberg |first5=Peter |title=Green space, urbanity, and health: how strong is the relation? |journal=Journal of Epidemiology & Community Health |date=1 July 2006 |volume=60 |issue=7 |pages=587–592 |doi=10.1136/jech.2005.043125 |pmid=16790830 |pmc=2566234 }}</ref>。歷史上以弱勢族群為主的社區通常較缺乏綠地，為政策（如過去美國住宅政策中的{{le|紅線制度|Redlining}}）與經濟不平等所致<ref>{{cite journal |last1=Rigolon |first1=Alessandro |last2=Németh |first2=Jeremy |title=What Shapes Uneven Access to Urban Amenities? Thick Injustice and the Legacy of Racial Discrimination in Denver's Parks |journal=Journal of Planning Education and Research |date=25 July 2018 |pages=0739456X1878925 |doi=10.1177/0739456X18789251 }}</ref>，近年的綠地規劃開始重視{{le|環境正義|Environmental justice}}與社區參與<ref name=":6">{{Cite web|title=Ep. 51: Urban Greening with Sandra Albro|url=https://sustainabilitydefined.com/urbangreening|access-date=2020-08-21|website=Sustainability Defined|archive-date=2021-04-30|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210430001808/https://sustainabilitydefined.com/urbangreening}}</ref>。清理污染與增設綠地可提升周圍住宅的價值，即{{le|環境縉紳化|Environmental gentrification}}<ref name="Banzhaf&McCormick">{{cite journal |last1=Banzhaf |first1=H. Spencer |last2=McCormick |first2=Eleanor |title=Moving beyond cleanup: Identifying the crucibles of environmental gentrification |journal=NCEE Working Paper Series |date=2006 |url=https://www.epa.gov/environmental-economics/working-paper-moving-beyond-cleanup-identifying-crucibles-environmental |access-date=2021-04-30 |archive-date=2021-03-19 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210319194235/https://www.epa.gov/environmental-economics/working-paper-moving-beyond-cleanup-identifying-crucibles-environmental }}</ref>，但此過程也可能有負面影響，使弱勢族群無力負擔房價而被迫遷出<ref name="Dooling 2009">{{Cite journal|last=Dooling|first=Sarah|date=2009|title=Ecological gentrification: A research agenda exploring justice in the city|journal=International Journal of Urban and Regional Research|pages=621–639}}</ref><ref name="Sieg_etal">{{cite journal |last1=Sieg |first1=Holger |last2=Smith |first2=V. Kerry |last3=Banzhaf |first3=H. Spencer |last4=Walsh |first4=Randall |title=Estimating the general equilibrium benefits of large changes in spatially delineated public goods |url=https://archive.org/details/sim_international-economic-review_2004-11_45_4/page/1047 |journal=International Economic Review |date=2004 |volume=45 |issue=4 |page=1047–77 |doi=10.1111/j.0020-6598.2004.00297.x }}</ref>。

